            <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">What is SheetLink?</h2>
                    <p>
                        SheetLink is a <strong>free, open-source web tool</strong> that helps you work with hyperlinks in Excel files.
                        Whether you need to extract URLs from spreadsheet cells or merge Title and URL columns into clickable links,
                        SheetLink makes it simple and fast.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-0">
                        All processing happens in-memory on the server, ensuring your files are never stored permanently.
                        We prioritize your privacy and security.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Key Features</h2>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><strong>Link Extraction:</strong> Extract hyperlinks from Excel cells and export URLs</li>
                        <li><strong>Link Merging:</strong> Combine Title and URL columns into clickable hyperlinks</li>
                        <li><strong>Privacy-First:</strong> All processing in-memory, no file storage</li>
                        <li><strong>Free & Open Source:</strong> No registration, no fees, Apache 2.0 license</li>
                        <li><strong>Excel Support:</strong> Works with .xlsx and .xls formats</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
                <div class="card-body p-4">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Technology</h2>
                    <p>
                        SheetLink is built with:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li><strong>ASP.NET Core 10.0</strong> (Blazor Server)</li>
                        <li><strong>DocumentFormat.OpenXml</strong> (Microsoft's official library)</li>
                        <li><strong>Docker</strong> for deployment</li>
                        <li><strong>Prometheus</strong> for metrics</li>
                    </ul>
